
CHAPTER 1: AN OVERVIEW OF THE INTERNET AND THE WEB

Group A: Short Questions 
1. Define the term “Protocol” in the context of the Internet.

 --> A protocol is a set of rules that decide how data is sent, received, and understood between devices on the Internet. Example: HTTP, FTP.

2. What is the primary difference between a Web Browser and a Search Engine?

 --> A web browser is software used to open websites (example: Chrome, Firefox).
  A search engine is a website that helps find information on the Internet (example: Google, Bing).

3. Define the World Wide Web (WWW).

--> The World Wide Web (WWW) is a collection of web pages that are connected through links and can be accessed using the Internet.
4. Differentiate between Front-end and Back-end development.
--> The  differentiate between Front-end and Back-end development.

here we go; 
# Front-end Development: It is interface of website deal with user. It use the languages like HTML,CSS, JavaScript,ect. It runs in web browser. 
It mainly handles buttons, forms, images, and menus,ect.

#Back-end Development: It deeals with the server side logic of a website, work behind the scenes. It focuses on the data processing and business logic. It uses languages like 
Java,Python, PHP,NOde.js,ect. It runs on the server. It handles databasess, authentication, and APIs.

