5. Explain the client-server architecture of the web with a neat diagram.
--> Client-server architecture is a model where two types of computers work together: client and server. 
-The client (web browser like Chrome) sends a request for a webpage. 
-The server (web server) recerives the request, processes it, and sends back the required webpage. 
